,"location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1865,"children_ids":["HD3997","HD3998","HD3999","HD4000","HD4001","HD4002","HD4003"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"Lived to ninety-two, outlived three of her children","body":"Laura Stiles Mansfield was born in 1787 in Connecticut and died in 1879 at age ninety-one or ninety-two — the longest-lived of her documented Stiles siblings. Of her seven Mansfield children, three died before age fourteen: Mary Elizabeth at thirteen in 1832, Laura Louisa at age two in 1823, and her youngest Laura at age two in 1828."},{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Two daughters named Laura, both dead at two","body":"Laura bore seven children with Ebenezer Mansfield. Her fourth child Laura Louisa was born 1821 and died at age two in 1823; five years later in 1826 she named a new daughter simply Laura, and that second Laura also died at age two — in November 1828."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FamilySearch person LZGF-NQY","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/tree/person/LZGF-NQY"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"laura-mansfield-1787"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM300","name":"Harmony Cemetery","county":"Otsego","state":"New York","country":"United States","findagrave_id":"65519","primary_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/65519/harmony-cemetery","hooker_connections":["HD3998","HD4009","I00547","I00551"],"notes":"Cemetery in Otsego County NY. Burial site of Isaac Mansfield (HD3998, 1815-1895) + wife Maria Hitchcock (I00547, 1819-1901) + son Charles Isaac Mansfield (HD4009, 1860-1903) — the New York-resident Mansfield branch."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}